      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"dark tunnel\" thing feels so patronizing sometimes. like, people always say there's light at the end, but what if there isn't? what if the only way to actually get the weight off my chest is to just... let go completely? i'm just so exhausted by the struggle to stay afloat when i've already sunk. it feels like the only way to finally get that \"quiet rest\" you mentioned is to just stop everything.",
